<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.2656224>
    dc:description "FIGURE 1. Eumunida multispina n. sp., holotype, male (cl 46.8 mm), CMFRI E.D.4.4.1.5, entire animal in dorsal view, showing colour in life. Right pereopod 4 damaged." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/2656224/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.2656226>
    dc:description "FIGURE 2. Eumunida multispina n. sp., holotype, male (cl 46.8 mm), CMF E.D.4.4.1.5, carapace, pleomeres 1 and 2, and cephalic appendages, dorsal view." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/2656226/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.2656228>
    dc:description "FIGURE 3. Eumunida multispina n. sp., holotype, male (cl 46.8 mm), CMFRI E.D.4.4.1.5.A, anterior part of carapace and eye, dorsal view; B, anterior part of carapace, cephalic appendages, lateral view." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/2656228/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.2656236>
    dc:description "FIGURE 7. Eumunida multispina n. sp., holotype, male (cl 46.8 mm), CMFRI E.D.4.4.1.5. A, left frontal part of carapace, eye and antenna, dorsal view; B, left anterolateral margin of carapace, dorsal view; C, left branchial margin of carapace, dorsal view; D, left antennal peduncle, lateral view; E, same, ventral view; F, left maxilliped 3, lateral view; G, distal part of propodus and dactylus of left pereopod 3, lateral view. Setae omitted." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/2656236/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.2656230>
    dc:description "FIGURE 4. Eumunida multispina n. sp., holotype, male (cl 46.8 mm), CMFRI E.D.4.4.1.5.A, thoracic sternum and coxae of pereopods 1–4; B, thoracic sternites 3 and 4; C, thoracic sternites 5 and 6, pleomeres 5 and 6, telson, and uropods." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/2656230/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.2656232>
    dc:description "FIGURE 5. Eumunida multispina n. sp., holotype, male (cl 46.8 mm), CMFRI E.D.4.4.1.5. A, merus and carpus of left cheliped and distal parts of meri to dactyli of left pereopods 2–4, dorsal view; B, merus of left cheliped, lateral view; C, same, ventral view; D, coxa to ischium of left cheliped, ventral view." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/2656232/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.2656234>
    dc:description "FIGURE 6. Eumunida multispina n. sp., holotype, male (cl 46.8 mm), CMFRI E.D.4.4.1.5. A, carpus and chela of left cheliped, dorsal view; B, chela of left cheliped ventral view; C, left pereopods 2–4, lateral view." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/2656234/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.2656238>
    dc:description "FIGURE 8. Eumunida multispina n. sp., paratype, male (cl 50.0 mm), CMFRI ED.4.4.1.5.1, entire animal in dorsal view (only right cheliped and right pereopod 3 are preserved)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/2656238/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.2656240>
    dc:description "FIGURE 9. Maximum Likelihood (ML) tree, showing relationships among five species of Eumunida, based on 16S rRNA gene sequence data. Heteroptychus scambus was used as an out-group for rooting the tree. The tree with the highest log likelihood (-866.27) is shown. Numbers on branches represent bootstrap values expressed in percentage (values<50% are not shown)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/2656240/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

